    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"498029\">Andreas Hindborg</span> <a href=\"#narrow/dm/498029,546447-dm/near/578376746\">said</a> to <span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"546447\">Benno Lossin</span>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi! I ran into something <code>pin_init</code>, wanted to check if you know or not. This code is building fine:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IrqHandler</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">mq</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Operations</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">RequestData</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NvmeRequest</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">queue</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">NvmeQueue</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>But this is failing complaining about missing bounds:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IrqHandler</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"k\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">mq</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"n\">Operations</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">RequestData</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">NvmeRequest</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">+</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"nb\">static</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">queue</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">NvmeQueue</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">T</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Build error:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Text only\"><pre><span></span><code>  RUSTC [M] drivers/block/rnvme/rnvme.o\nerror[E0277]: the trait bound `T: Operations` is not satisfied\n   --&gt; /home/aeh/src/linux-rust/rnvme-v6.19/drivers/block/rnvme/nvme_queue.rs:293:16\n    |\n293 |     queue: Arc&lt;NvmeQueue&lt;T&gt;&gt;,\n    |                ^^^^^^^^^^^^ the trait `Operations` is not implemented for `T`\n    |\nnote: required by a bound in `NvmeQueue`\n   --&gt; /home/aeh/src/linux-rust/rnvme-v6.19/drivers/block/rnvme/nvme_queue.rs:37:32\n    |\n 37 | pub(crate) struct NvmeQueue&lt;T: mq::Operations&lt;RequestData = NvmeRequest&gt; + 'static&gt; {\n    |                                ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ required by this bound in `NvmeQueue`\nhelp: consider restricting type parameter `T` with trait `Operations`\n    |\n289 | struct IrqHandler&lt;T: kernel::block::mq::Operations&gt;\n    |                    +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It looks like the bounds in the <code>where</code> clause are discarded?</p>\n</blockquote>",
